abstract: President Donald Trump will use next week’s State of the Union to promote what he calls the “Great American comeback,” according to a senior administration official.
snippet: President Donald Trump will use next week’s State of the Union to promote what he calls the “Great American comeback,” according to a senior administration official.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump will use next week’s State of the Union to promote what he calls the “Great American comeback,” according to a senior administration official.
headline_main: Trump to Tout U.S. 'Comeback' at State of the Union Speech
headline_print_headline: Trump to Tout U.S. 'Comeback' at State of the Union Speech

abstract: There is no question, Sen. Lamar Alexander said, that President Donald Trump actions were “inappropriate” when he asked Ukraine's leader to investigate Democratic rival Joe Biden.
snippet: There is no question, Sen. Lamar Alexander said, that President Donald Trump actions were “inappropriate” when he asked Ukraine's leader to investigate Democratic rival Joe Biden.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — There is no question, Sen. Lamar Alexander said, that President Donald Trump actions were “inappropriate” when he asked Ukraine's leader to investigate Democratic rival Joe Biden.
headline_main: GOP Senators Seek to Acquit Trump Without Condoning Conduct
headline_print_headline: GOP Senators Seek to Acquit Trump Without Condoning Conduct

abstract: In May 2019, President Donald Trump asked then-national security adviser John Bolton to help make sure Ukraine's newly elected leader met with Rudy Giuliani about investigations he sought into Democrats, according to an unpublished manuscript of Bolton's book.
snippet: In May 2019, President Donald Trump asked then-national security adviser John Bolton to help make sure Ukraine's newly elected leader met with Rudy Giuliani about investigations he sought into Democrats, according to an unpublished manuscript of B...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In May 2019, President Donald Trump asked then-national security adviser John Bolton to help make sure Ukraine's newly elected leader met with Rudy Giuliani about investigations he sought into Democrats, according to an unpublished manuscript of Bolton's book.
headline_main: Bolton: Trump Asked Me to Ensure Zelenskiy, Giuliani Met
headline_print_headline: Bolton: Trump Asked Me to Ensure Zelenskiy, Giuliani Met

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates kicked off a final, frenetic weekend of campaigning ahead of the Iowa caucuses, which will begin the battle to take on President Donald Trump in November.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates kicked off a final, frenetic weekend of campaigning ahead of the Iowa caucuses, which will begin the battle to take on President Donald Trump in November.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Democratic presidential candidates kicked off a final, frenetic weekend of campaigning ahead of the Iowa caucuses, which will begin the battle to take on President Donald Trump in November.
headline_main: 2020 Candidates Brace for Frenzied, Final Weekend in Iowa
headline_print_headline: 2020 Candidates Brace for Frenzied, Final Weekend in Iowa

abstract: A federal filing showing spending through December provides the most detailed description yet of how Mr. Bloomberg deployed his wealth in a quest for the presidency. The bulk went to advertising.
snippet: A federal filing showing spending through December provides the most detailed description yet of how Mr. Bloomberg deployed his wealth in a quest for the presidency. The bulk went to advertising.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Michael R. Bloomberg put more than $200 million of his personal fortune into his presidential campaign by the end of December, with the overwhelming bulk of that sum going to a mammoth advertising campaign on television and online, according to Mr. Bloomberg’s first campaign finance disclosure with the Federal Election Commission.

abstract: In terms of actual policy, probably not very much.
snippet: In terms of actual policy, probably not very much.
lead_paragraph: At this point, the Democratic presidential nomination is very much up in the air. Not only is it unclear who will be the nominee; it’s unclear whether the nominee will be a centrist like Joe Biden or Amy Klobuchar, or a representative of the party’s left like Bernie Sanders or Elizabeth Warren. Whoever wins, there will be much wailing and gnashing of teeth from the other side.

abstract: John Delaney, the longest-running Democratic candidate in the 2020 presidential race, is ending his campaign after pouring millions of his own money into an effort that failed to resonate with voters.
snippet: John Delaney, the longest-running Democratic candidate in the 2020 presidential race, is ending his campaign after pouring millions of his own money into an effort that failed to resonate with voters.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — John Delaney, the longest-running Democratic candidate in the 2020 presidential race, is ending his campaign after pouring millions of his own money into an effort that failed to resonate with voters.
headline_main: Delaney, Longest-Running Democratic Candidate, Ends 2020 Bid

abstract: After steadily rising in popularity over the last several weeks, former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg appears to have surpassed U.S. Senator Elizabeth Warren among registered voters for the 2020 Democratic nomination, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national public opinion poll released on Thursday.
snippet: After steadily rising in popularity over the last several weeks, former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg appears to have surpassed U.S. Senator Elizabeth Warren among registered voters for the 2020 Democratic nomination, according to a Reuter...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — After steadily rising in popularity over the last several weeks, former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg appears to have surpassed U.S. Senator Elizabeth Warren among registered voters for the 2020 Democratic nomination, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national public opinion poll released on Thursday.
headline_main: Movin' on Up: Bloomberg Glides Past Warren to No.3 in Democratic Race-Reuters/Ipsos
headline_print_headline: Movin' on Up: Bloomberg Glides Past Warren to No.3 in Democratic Race-Reuters/Ipsos
